                            <container4
                                cq:styleIds="[1653545847150,1653242825678,1653545825687,1653545835982]"
                                jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/container/v2/container">
                                <title2_copy
                                    cq:styleIds="[1659545825678,1651545824678,1651545825694]"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2024-05-08T09:49:53.025-04:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="VALENSX5"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    jcr:title="Waiting on the rain"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/title/v2/title"
                                    type="h2"
                                    variant="h"/>
                                <text2_copy
                                    cq:styleIds="[1659545835858]"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2023-01-24T15:46:00.469-05:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="schafsm"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/text/v2/text"
                                    text="&lt;p>For many children, a rainstorm is nothing special.&lt;/p>&#xa;&lt;p>Maybe it’s an opportunity to spend the afternoon inside watching movies or playing games. An excuse to debut a new raincoat at school; a chance to splash in puddles.&lt;/p>&#xa;&lt;p>For Fredrick Bailey, a rainstorm was life.&lt;/p>&#xa;&lt;p>Bailey, 31, recalls his childhood in LaGrange, Georgia, living in a home without electricity or running water. With both parents suffering from drug addiction and his father often gone, a 12-year-old Bailey placed a bucket on the front porch and prayed for rain – precious water he needed to wash his clothes. One winter night, scrubbing his jeans with rainwater and a bar of soap, Bailey had enough.&lt;/p>&#xa;&lt;p>“I told myself, I convinced myself, life is better than this,” Bailey says. “And I wanted to experience that better life.”&lt;/p>&#xa;&lt;p>Today, Bailey is truly experiencing that better life. He credits an intervention from national education nonprofit&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.communitiesinschools.org/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; title=&quot; Communities In Schools &quot;>Communities In Schools&lt;/a>&amp;nbsp;(CIS) as the catalyst both academically and on a personal level, that enabled him to change the trajectory of his future.&lt;/p>&#xa;"
                                    textIsRich="true"/>
                            </container4>
                            <video
                                cq:styleIds="[0]"
                                jcr:created="{Date}2023-01-24T15:52:42.090-05:00"
                                jcr:createdBy="schafsm"
                                jcr:lastModified="{Date}2023-09-12T02:06:01.679-04:00"
                                jcr:lastModifiedBy="kumarvx60"
                                jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/video/v2/video"
                                autoPlay="true"
                                brightcoveAutoPlay="false"
                                btnText="Watch 2:09"
                                description="&lt;p>The Promise of Communities In Schools&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;"
                                descriptiveIframeTitle="AbbVie Partner Spotlight: The Promise of Communities In Schools"
                                fileReference="/content/dam/abbvie-com2/images/stories/the-value-of-education-from-a-dim-reality-to-a-bright-future/value-of-education-video-thumbnail.jpg"
                                imgAlt="AbbVie Partner Spotlight: The Promise of Communities In Schools"
                                loopVideo="false"
                                showBrightcoveControls="false"
